==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Examiner
<hw>Ex*am"in*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who examines,
tries, or inspects; one who interrogates; an officer or person charged
with the duty of making an examination; <as>as, an <ex>examiner</ex> of
students for a degree; an <ex>examiner</ex> in chancery, in the patent
office, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Examinership</ent>⟦br⟧
